The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to generate reading comprehension questions of designated difficulty levels. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
